	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Mountain <sic>Collage</sic>&#44; Cote St Catharine</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>15 August 1865</date>.</p>
				<p>My dear Sir&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Yours of <date>13th</date> ult. Found<lb/> me out of town&#8212;like yourself&#44; I have<lb/> been moving about a little&#45;though<lb/> my circuit has not extended to <placeName>Yankee&#45;<lb/>land</placeName>.  I was sorry to find you had<lb/> been suffering somewhat from lungs<lb/> &#38; throat.  Being myself somewhat<lb/> delicate in those regions&#44; and a<lb/> fellow feeling making us wondrous<lb/> kind&#44; I felt for you&#44; and trust<lb/> that your trip south has helped<lb/> completely to restore you.  With reference<lb/> to your visit to <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>&#8212;had I been<lb/> in time I should have urged you to<lb/> continue in office as President of<lb/> your district of Benai Berith&#44; for since<lb/> this <sic>organisation</sic>&#44; which I view with<lb/> anything but favor&#44; has assumed its<lb/> present proportions&#44; I suppose we<lb/> <hi rend="underline">must</hi> look after it&#44; lest our humble</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>modest pious &#38;c reform brethren use<lb/> it as a tool&#8212;a terrible one too&#8212;<lb/> against orthodoxy.  But I <hi rend="underline">hate</hi> the<lb/> very idea of a Jewish secret society&#8212;<lb/> no Roman Catholic prelate ever hated<lb/> masonry orangeism Ribbonism or any<lb/> other secret ism more than I abhor<lb/> such an organisation among us&#45;<lb/> or one at all approaching these Christian<lb/> religious or political secret societies.<lb/>  But I am not going to trouble you<lb/> with a disquisition on them&#44; especially<lb/> as I have an abominable pen which<lb/> will stick into the paper&#44; and being<lb/> away from home I cannot change it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I will&#44; as usual&#44; bring the<lb/> circular you enclosed me prominently<lb/> before our small circle here&#8212;I fear<lb/> with but little success.  We have<lb/> too many Polish &#38; German brethren<lb/> for <hi rend="underline">English</hi>&#45;books&#8212;though not<lb/> for synagogue purposes&#44; and I don&#39;t<lb/> know what I should do without<lb/> them.  I sometimes think I am</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>as much a <hi rend="underline"><persName>Pollock</persName></hi> as any of them.<lb/>  <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I gave <persName>Sarah Joseph</persName> your<lb/> message&#44; and she wishes I believe to<lb/> make an enclosure for you in this.<lb/>  If she is &#8220;up to time&#8221;&#44; well&#44; if not&#44; you<lb/> will get it another time.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I heard lately that <persName>Mr<lb/> Dd Judah</persName> of <placeName>Baltimore</placeName> has gone the way<lb/> of all the earth.  He was <hi rend="underline">nominally</hi><lb/> my agent for that city&#44; and when he<lb/> died&#44; held some books or proceeds thereof<lb/> on hand.  Would you kindly inform me<lb/> as to the best means of proceeding to<lb/> obtain one or the other&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With best wishes&#44; and hoping<lb/> to hear soon from you</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">I remain yours faithfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
		</body>
